EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to public utilities; requiring the Public Utilities
Commission of Nevada to adopt regulations to require a
public utility to make available to the public certain
reports containing information regarding terminations of
utility service to residential customers; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Public Utilities Commission of Nevada to adopt or
2 amend certain regulations relating to a public utility terminating the gas, water or
3 electric utilities of a residential customer. (NRS 704.1835) This bill requires the
4 Commission to adopt regulations that require a public utility to make available to
5 the public a quarterly report concerning such terminations of utility services.
6 Specifically, this bill requires that the report include: (1) the total number of
7 monthly terminations of utility services of residential customers during the previous
8 quarter; and (2) aggregated information concerning the residential customers whose
9 utility service was terminated, which must include the zip code of such residences.
